## Go further

### A. Order matters

This version is wrong:

```python
score = 95

if score >= 70:
    print("Pass")
elif score >= 90:
    print("Excellent")
```

Why? Because `95` matches the first condition, so Python never reaches the second one.

Better:

```python
score = 95

if score >= 90:
    print("Excellent")
elif score >= 70:
    print("Pass")
else:
    print("Needs work")
```

### B. Exact equality vs ranges

```python
hour = 12

if hour == 12:
    print("Noon")
else:
    print("Not noon")
```

### C. Boolean variables can be used directly

```python
is_raining = True

if is_raining:
    print("Bring an umbrella")
else:
    print("No umbrella needed")
```

